  "text": "Over the last decade, RGB-D sensors have made rapid development, such as Microsoft Kinect, Intel Leap Motion and ASUS Xtion Pro. They enable a variety of applications based on the depth image of the scenes, for instance, pose estimation [CITATION_1] and scene understanding [CITATION_2] . Moreover, object tracking using depth information plays a vital role in several applications such as multimedia contexts, body-parts movements, video streaming, healthcare systems and smart indoor security systems [CITATION_3] .",
